{"ts":"2026-06-26T06:10:40.783Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining Page Structure**\n\nOkay, so I've confirmed the navigation data is straightforward. Now, I'm focusing on drafting the actual content and structural elements for those three core pages. My plan is to start laying out the foundation now, without overcomplicating things.\n\n\n**Planning Page Design**\n\nI'm now diving deep into the individual page designs, especially the Enterprise AI Blueprint. The focus is on a high-quality user experience that includes beautiful custom SVG visuals, interactive elements, and an intuitive roadmap/workflow. I'm prioritizing adherence to the GFF design system and exploring a visual Readiness Score dashboard with interactive dimensions for the Blueprint page.\n\n\n**Designing the Blueprint**\n\nI'm expanding the Enterprise AI Blueprint page with specific, interactive elements. I'm incorporating an audit profile with recommended solutions and targets. I'm also planning the 90-day sovereign roadmap, including diagnostics, co-design, and deployment phases, to use an accordion or timeline. Finally, I'll leverage high-quality components and icons from `lucide-react`. I'll link to `/build/blueprint` where users can generate their own.\n\n\n**Showcasing Registry Elements**\n\nI'm now outlining the Sovereign Accelerator Registry, focusing on a compelling hero section. It features the \"Tier 1.5 • Curated Agentic Assets\" category and \"Deploy battle-tested, pre-audited agent patterns\" description. Key features include a filterable registry, interactive preview with cognitive flow schema, system instructions, and a \"Deploy to GFF Sandbox\" approach. I'm also planning a deployment flow diagram for `/platforms/marketplace/page`.\n\n\n**Crafting Control Center**\n\nI'm now focusing on the Control Center page, aiming for a \"Tier 4\" category with a \"Unified Cockpit & Governance\" theme. I'm prioritizing an interactive cockpit console dashboard to simulate operational observability, using a clickable grid for agent fleet status updates, and actionable modules for security, spend, and compliance. The design must be a high-quality, simulated dashboard.\n\n\n**Simulating Observability Controls**\n\nI'm now integrating active, sandboxed, and complete status checks with the Control Center. I'm focusing on interactive governance guardrail policies, like PII redaction and SOC2 compliance, to showcase real-time security enforcement. I'll visualize spend and resource allocation with interactive analytics. I'm also ensuring the design is consistent with existing breadcrumbs and styling. I also have to find the correct directory for the page, which I will do shortly.\n\n\n"}}
